  <title translate="true">ObjectVerticalIntersectLength</title>
  <body>
    <header>
      <para styleclass="Heading1"><text styleclass="Heading1" translate="true">ObjectVerticalIntersectLength</text></para>
    </header>
    <para styleclass="Normal"><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true">For objects drawn on the top view of the model with two Z coordinates, </text><text styleclass="Strong" translate="true">ObjectVerticalIntersectLength</text><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true"> returns the vertical length of intersection between the object and the current cell or element.</text></para>
    <para styleclass="Normal"><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true">This function in combination with </text><link displaytype="text" defaultstyle="true" type="topiclink" href="ObjectVerticalLength" styleclass="Normal" translate="true">ObjectVerticalLength</link><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true"> can be used to distribute a value among several layers. ObjectVerticalIntersectLength/ObjectVerticalLength is the fraction of the vertical extent of an object intersected by the current cell or element.</text></para>
  </body>
